BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:DousKj0YDh5KXKS5EnUXP
SUMMARY:Spring Refresh featuring Screen Printing!
DTSTAMP:20260326T120801Z
DTSTART:20260330T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Spring Refresh: A Screen Printing Party and Clothing Drive  \\n
	Come connect!\\nJoin us for Spring Refresh\\\, a hands-on event where neig
	hbors come together to create\\\, give\\\, and care for one another. This 
	evening is both a fun activity and an opportunity to show up for our commu
	nity!  \\nScreen Printing! \\nBring a piece of light colored clothing to p
	articipate in screen-printing fun. PNA’s amazing Woodshop built two custom
	 screen-printing presses for the night. (We will also have white t-shirts 
	available for sale.) \\nChoose from two designs: \\nThe iconic PhinneyWood
	 Heart – A bold\\\, graphic symbol of neighborhood pride and love for loca
	l small businesses.\\nThe PNA Orca\\\, designed by PNA Art Club member Chi
	no – A powerful symbol of shared knowledge\\\, care across generations\\\,
	 and community traditions. \\nLet’s wear our values and tell the story of 
	a community that shows up for one another. \\nSpring Clothing Drive for th
	e Hot Meal Program \\nAs we gather\\\, we’ll also be collecting clean\\\, 
	lightly worn clothing for adults to support the PNA’s Hot Meal Program Com
	munity Closet. Men’s clothing is especially needed. Some of our most reque
	sted items include: \\n\\nNew socks and underwear\\nLightly used shoes and
	 boots\\nMen’s pants\\\, especially larger sizes\\n\\nLast year\\\, the Ho
	t Meal Program served over 21\\\,000 free meals\\\, while also connecting 
	neighbors to medical care\\\, haircuts\\\, and essential resources.\\nThan
	ks to you\\\, this support is possible. When you bring clothing or donate\
	\\, you’re directly helping meet real needs in our neighborhood. \\nTunes\
	\\, Snacks & Lemonade \\nEnjoy music\\\, light snacks\\\, and refreshing l
	emonade while you print\\\, connect\\\, and give back. \\nWho’s Invited \\
	nYou!\\nThis all-ages event is open to neighbors\\\, PNA Members\\\, local
	 PhinneyWood small business owners\\\, and anyone curious about the PNA. C
	ome meet your neighbors\\\, learn what’s happening\\\, and be part of some
	thing meaningful. \\nEvent Details \\nMonday\\\, March 30\\n5:00–7:00 pm\\
	nPhinney Center – Room 7\\n6532 Phinney Ave N\\\, Seattle\\\, WA 98103  \\
	nFree for members \\n$10 for non-members \\nDonations welcome to support t
	he PNA programs such as the Hot Meal Program.  \\nSpots are limited—regist
	er soon to reserve yours! \\n  \\nRSVP\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/ev
	ent/screen-printing-party/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/screen-printing-party/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\
	\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
